why git/github?
central codebase banana taki multiple log jo ek project me envolve hai sab read,write kar paye aur edit kar paye

git :-> main codebase ka management tool
GitHub:-> same git waali functionality bas ye website ke form me milegi

git :-> iske bina git(management) ke process nahi kiye ja sakte { ye commandline sehi chalega}
GitHub :-> ye sirf git (management) ka online tareeka hai isliye isse chalaneke liye Git install hona chahiye { kuki ye website  hai, to ye aap google chrome ya kisi aur browser se chala sakteho}


 Understanding GitHub:
1)New repository   ==  new folder
2)History
3)Branches
4)Fork            == complete copy
5)GitHub issues section                       GitHub issues == complaints , commit = save
6)Command line interface
7)GitHub pages

pencil mark edit file = yaha edid kar sakte file me fir history me changes check kar sakte ho

#########Branching
this is probability 1 brach linked from main branch with some changes or additional info lekin main branch same rahengi jo pahile thi bina changes aur additional info ke
branching is needed when there are multiple possibilities 

########### pull request
branch me changes kiye gye main file me merge karne ke liye pull request use hoga.
pull request hamesha owner ki side se hoga
isme kisse kisme changes comapre karke pull karne wo bhi set kar sakte
example:

master                         |         probability 1
l1 ek din mar jayega           |         l1 ek din mar jayega
l2 kutte ki  muat              |         l2 something else

is case me dispute aayega merge nahi hoga github confirm which one should be put in final version in l2
isse resolve karne ke liye pull request karke resolve conflict karo aur jo nahi chahiye wo  hata do 

$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$  Fork
fork kisi aur repository to complete copy kar ke tumhe dega jisme tum add ya update changes kar sakte ho ye changes jis account se fork kiya hai usko bhi jayenge aur wo chahe
to changes to repository me merge kar sakta hai


